# 詞：銀包

1. 我個銀包唔知邊度去咗，好驚係唔係遺落喺巴士度。 (I don't know where my wallet went; I'm very afraid I might have left it on the bus.)
2. 佢買咗咁多嘢，銀包仲有得剩，真係好威水。 (He bought so many things and still has money left in his wallet; he's really impressive.)
3. 呢個銀包係我阿媽送畀我嘅生日禮物，好靚。 (This wallet is a birthday gift from my mom; it's very beautiful.)
4. 你唔好將銀包放喺度，有細路仔可能會偷走。 (Don't leave your wallet here; a child might steal it.)
5. 我個銀包被扒手搶走咗，真係好倒楣。 (My wallet was snatched by a pickpocket; I'm really unlucky.)
6. 雖然個銀包舊咗，但係用得好耐，仲未壞。 (Although the wallet is old, it has lasted a long time and hasn't broken yet.)
7. 你個銀包入面有幾多錢？我哋要出街食飯。 (How much money is in your wallet? We're going out to eat.)
8. 我唔使帶銀包，因為我都有用手機支付。 (I don't need to bring my wallet because I use mobile payment.)
9. 個銀包入面有張銀行卡同埋幾張現金。 (There is a bank card and some cash inside the wallet.)
10. 我哋應該換個新銀包，個舊嘅已經好鬆咗。 (We should get a new wallet; the old one is already very loose.) [end of text]


